Per {{WP:NOTNEWS}}, we don't write as if we were writing for a newspaper, awaiting the release of updated information. Authorities not "(suspecting) foul play" is unsuitable for encyclopedia writing. We write facts that will not change. Encyclopedia style is different from any other writing style. Don't be afraid of short sentences. We don't write facts just because we know them {{WP:NOT EVERYTHING}}: "Information should not be included in this encyclopedia solely because it is true or useful."

/* Alcohol and drug addiction */Removed unnecessary word. One is not "completely" sober. That is tantamount to asserting that someone is "completely pregnant." One is either sober or not. To be sober is to be completely sober.

/* Alcohol and drug addiction */Restructured sentence to comply with encyclopedia style. Removed that Perry had been sober since 2021. Sobriety is a fragile state that can change in a moment. It cannot be stated that someone has been sober since two years ago with any authority, even if a third-party publishes it. The standard of proof for an encyclopedia is different from that of any other media form.
